"What's happened to me?" he thought. It wasn't a dream. His room, a proper human room although a little too small, lay peacefully between its four familiar walls. A collection of textile samples lay spread out on the table and above it there hung a picture that he had recently cut out of an illustrated magazine and housed in a nice, gilded frame.

Gregor then turned to look out the window at the dull weather. Drops of rain could be heard hitting the pane, which made him feel quite sad.

<div class="continue">[[Continue|Passage 3]]</div>

